                              Point 7.9: substring()
                              ======================
                              
substring() is used to take a small part from a String.

String s = "Spring";
System.out.println(s.substring(0, 3));

Output:
Spr



                    Important Rule
                    substring(startIndex, endIndex)

startIndex is included
endIndex is excluded

Meaning:
Start index character will be taken.
End index character will NOT be taken.


                        Very Important Formula
substring(0, 3) takes index 0, 1, 2
substring(1, 4) takes index 1, 2, 3
substring(2) takes index 2 till end


                                        Example 1

String s = "Spring";
System.out.println(s.substring(0, 3));

Index diagram:
==============

Character:  S   p   r   i   n   g
Index:      0   1   2   3   4   5

Now:    s.substring(0, 3)

Means:
            Start from index 0
            Go till index 3
            But do not include index 3
So it takes:
Index 0 → S
Index 1 → p
Index 2 → r

OUTPUT:
Spr

Index 3 has i, but it is not included.
